headline: Moody’s Named #1 in Chartis RiskTech100® for the Fourth Year Running
summary: NEW YORK, October 23, 2025--Moody’s Corporation (NYSE: MCO) has been named the #1 company in the 2026 Chartis RiskTech100® report, marking the firm’s fourth straight year at the top of the ranking.

headline: MCO Q3 Deep Dive: Multi-Segment Growth Driven by Issuance, AI, and Margin Expansion
summary: Credit rating agency Moody's (NYSE:MCO) reported Q3 CY2025 results topping the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 10.7% year on year to $2.01 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $3.92 per share was 6.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Moody's (MCO): Margin Improvement Reinforces Bullish Narratives Despite Valuation Premium
summary: Moody’s (MCO) reported strong earnings with net profit margins climbing to 29.2%, up from last year’s 28.3%. Earnings per share continued to impress, with recent growth of 14.7% over the past year. This outpaced the company’s 5-year annual average of -0.1%. The numbers show high-quality earnings and improved profitability. However, with revenue forecast to grow 6.9% per year and earnings set for 13.1% annual growth, both figures are expected to trail the broader US market. See our full...
